data.title: Conti Federal secures $97.3M contract to build new facilities at Schofield Barracks, Hawaii.
data.description: An American company, Conti Federal Services, known for its expertise in military construction and infrastructure projects for the U.S. government, has secured a significant contract worth $97.3 million from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers. This contract, assigned by the Pacific Ocean Division, Honolulu District, entails the construction of Company Operations Facilities at South Range Schofield Barracks. The project, falling under the design-bid-build category for Military Construction, aims to provide five new facilities.

data.title: Private equity deal value reached a record US$310b, with exit activity rising 40%. Fundraising stayed soft but could improve with new retail channels.
data.description: Progress in deals was accelerated due to decreasing valuation disparities and better funding circumstances, resulting in the highest deployment numbers on record. Exit operations saw a significant 40% increase compared to the previous year, primarily due to the robust performance of IPO markets. While fundraising activity was relatively subdued, the introduction of new retail avenues and expanded access to the US 401(k) system hint at future potential for growth in this area.

data.title: Novo Nordisk offers $9 billion counteroffer for Metsera, challenging Pfizer's $4.9 billion acquisition.
data.description: Metsera Inc. (NASDAQ: MTSR) recently received an unexpected acquisition offer from Novo Nordisk A/S (NYSE: NVO), with the proposal deemed a "Superior Company Proposal" compared to Metsera's current Merger Agreement with Pfizer Inc (NYSE: PFE), who had previously agreed to purchase Metsera for $47.50 per share in cash, totaling around $4.9 billion. This deal would provide Pfizer with a set of unique oral and injectable incretin, non-incretin, and combination therapy candidates. Novo Nordisk's proposal is outlined in two phases, with the initial phase involving a payment of $56.50 per share in cash to Metsera upon the finalization of a definitive agreement, along with additional amounts pertaining to Metsera employee equity and transaction costs.
